<p>In an item (A) which handle the position of his sons (B, BB, BBB) (e.g.: a RowLayout) you don‚Äôt have to put anchors.fill: parent to one of the sons, if you do this the son‚Äôs position management will be broken.</p>

<p>In this example the rectangle B is used to do a background which is wrong, the right solution is to put this rectangle at the root, as a parent of the RowLayout.</p>

<h2 id="sourcejavascript">[source,javascript]</h2>
<p>RowLayout {
 	id: A
    Rectangle {
    	id: B
        anchors.fill: parent // don‚Äôt do this !
        color: ‚Äúred‚Äù
    }</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>Rectangle {
	id: BB
}

Rectangle {
	id: BBB
} }
</code></pre></div></div>

